text: It’s a hawker Center. Don’t expect super clean tables and NO birds. Nice breakfast place especially for Malay food stalls. Very obvious which ones are the popular ones. A few non halal food stalls. A very short ride (5mins) to ECP via Bedok underpass which u will end up near OBS campus.
So far, the food is tasty and worth the price, but the place is somewhat untidy and not very clean atmosphere.

Waited for more than 30 min for the satay. Satay meat - beef & mutton - were very tasty. The satay gravy was thick & yummy with crunchy peanuts. 👍🏼 However, satay was not well grilled as there parts burnt & others uncooked. 👎🏼 Hokkien Mee was good! 👍🏼 We dabao-ed Roti John & found it to be miserably thin. 👎🏼
Great local authentic fares but limited dinning seats or under umbrella shades 😁
Lots of delicious Halal food here! I love it... The food is good and tastes great! There are many choices of food, kueh and drinks here. This place is a legend! Highly recommended!
